result.execSummary:
The defendant Morris K Bennett was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Attempt Attempt Take and Drive Vehicle w/o Consent, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.23(2).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Morris K Bennett in court with attorney Susan Marie Roth.  Defendant Morris K Bennett in custody.  Lucy Kronforst appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, Defense, and Defendant.    The Court sentenced the defendant to a TOTAL LENGTH of imprisonment of 2 years, concurrent to case 14CF5210 but consecutive to any other sentence.
The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prisons is 1 year with credit for 190 days time served.  The Court orders the defendant to serve a maximum term of EXTENDED SUPERVISION of 1 year.

Conditions of Extended Supervision to be determined by the Dept. of Corrections, but to include:

*Alcohol and drug assessment and comply with any treatment deemed necessary by the department.
*Absolute sobriety.
*Random urine screens.  No positive results.
*No illegal drugs.
*No controlled substances without valid prescription.
*No contact with drug community.
*No contact with Valerie K.
*Seek and maintain full time employment.
*Obtain high school diploma or GED.
*Cognitive Behavior Therapy.

Court ordered restitution in the amount of $664.92 to be paid to Valerie K.

- Defendant ordered no DNA sample or surcharge in this case as it was ordered in case 14CF5210.
- Defendant advised that he may never again possess firearms or weapons.
- Civil rights suspended until reinstated.  Order received and filed.
- Pay all costs, surcharges and restitution out of up to 25% prison funds, any balance as a condition of ES.  If not paid, a civil judgment to be entered.
- Defendant does qualify for the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program after serving 1 year initial confinement in cases 15CF55 and 14CF5210.

The Court does object to expungment in this case.
